        <para><para xml:id="idg-all-networking-moving_from_dvr_deployments-xml-4"><phrase><phrase/></phrase></para></para>


         <sidebar xml:id="converting_older_hos_to_non_dvr"><title>Moving from DVR deployments to non_DVR</title><para>If you have an older deployment of &kw-hos; which is using DVR as a
                default and you are attempting to move to non_DVR, make sure you follow these steps: 
                </para>
<orderedlist>
                    <listitem><para>Remove all your existing DVR routers and their workloads. Make sure to
                        remove interfaces, floating ips and gateways, if applicable.
                        </para>
<screen >neutron router-interface-delete &lt;router-name&gt; &lt;subnet-name&gt;/&lt;subnet-id&gt;
neutron floatingip-disassociate &lt;floatingip-id&gt; &lt;private-port-id&gt;
neutron router-gateway-clear &lt;router-name&gt; &lt;ext-net-name&gt;/&lt;ext-net-id&gt;</screen></listitem>
                    <listitem><para>Then delete the router.
                        </para>
<screen >neutron router-delete &lt;router-name&gt;</screen></listitem>
                    <listitem><para>Before you create any non_DVR router make sure that l3-agents and
                        metadata-agents are not running in any compute host. You can run the command
                            <literal>neutron agent-list</literal> to see if there are any
                        neutron-l3-agent running in any compute-host in your deployment. 
                        </para>
<para>You must disable neutron-l3-agent and neutron-metadata-agent on every
                            compute host by running the following commands:
                            </para>
<screen >$ neutron agent-list
